  "bio": [
    "Sergio Stevanato is the president of the Stevanato Group, a medical packaging firm based in Piombino Dese, Italy.",
    "Founded by his father Giovanni in 1949, the company is now run by his sons Franco and Marco, who serve as CEO and vice chairman, respectively.",
    "Now, the Stevanato Group is the world's largest producer of insulin pen cartridges and the second-largest of glass vials.",
    "The company started out making glass bottles for wine and perfume.",
    "In June 2020, Stevanato won a contract to supply 100 million glass vials for up to 2 billion doses of Covid-19 vaccines."
  ],
  "about": [
    "He owns a winery in northeast Italy, Tenuta Stella, named after the Stevanato Group's original name, Soffieria Stella.",
    "In 2007 he was appointed a Cavaliere del Lavoro, one of Italy's highest civilian honors."
  ]
